.TH "vfs_readlink" 9 "vfs_readlink" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vfs_readlink \- copy symlink body into userspace buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vfs_readlink
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "char __user *buffer "  ","
.BI "int buflen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
dentry on which to get symbolic link
.IP "buffer" 12
user memory pointer
.IP "buflen" 12
size of buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Does not touch atime.  That's up to the caller if necessary

Does not call security hook.
